    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-29T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-29T20:00:00-05:00" n="320"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1352b.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-29T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 29, 1914, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Please explain to the Minister for Foreign Affairs that the action taken by the
                        <hi rend="italic">Machias</hi> should not be regarded as indicative of any
                    hostility towards the Bordas Government much less of favor to the
                    revolutionists, but that it was considered by this Government as a step
                    necessary for the protection of non-combatants in Puerto Plata.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
